08/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano signed a memorandum on economic and financial policies, part of a three-year poverty reduction and growth programme, with the IMF on Tuesday (7 January). Nano says it affirms policies of economic and social stability and constitutes an important commitment to the IMF. The document envisions economic growth of 6 per cent in 2003, an inflation rate of between 2 per cent and 4 per cent and a budget deficit of 6.5 per cent. Also Tuesday, Nano met with President Alfred Moisiu to discuss institutional co-operation between the ruling and opposition parties. (ATA, Albanian TV -07/01/03)
